      "writtenOn": "2020-11-15T20:08:23Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Fact 1: the refresh tasks are submitted every minute.\nFact 2: by default, if this fails transiently, it\u0027ll be retried by task queue automatically.\n\n\u003d\u003e\n\nIf LUCI config is transiently unavailable for N minutes,\nthere will be N tasks per LUCI project hammering LUCI config, and doing essentially the same thing.\n\n\nSo, better to always return permanent failure here regardless of transience of error or not, since we don\u0027t automatic need retries. I think something like this should work:\n\nerr :\u003d RefreshConfig(ctx, project)\nif transient.Tag.In(err) {\n  errors.Log(ctx, err)\n  return errors.Reason(\"failed to refresh config for %s: %s\", project, err).Err()\n}\nreturn err",
      "revId": "fffa7e7b7b0e9e931e24411c090e8c08dd9b42ff",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
