      "message": "we don\u0027t *always* have to annotate errors, the most important reason to capture stack as early as possible as well as mark it as transient (if it is such). errors.Annotate, erorrs.Reason, errors.New (from our errors package) do this job.\nAlso, FYI, errors.Log(ctx, err) will helpfully provide stacktrace (useful in tests/debug logs on server)\n\nOn higher levels, like here where error comes form getAllProjects which you can trust to ensure errors it returns already captured stack, there is little advantage in more annotation -- I\u0027d just forward `err` as is.",
