      "writtenOn": "2020-11-15T20:08:23Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "every time DS flakes, you\u0027d cause extra load on LUCI Config with slimmer chances of success. Bailing with error is better, IMO.\n\nI see that bool return value is better than (bool, error), but you can also merge this part into updateProject, say\nupdateProjectIfNeeded(ctx, project, externalHash)\n\nFor a stronger reason to do this see L154 comment.",
      "revId": "fffa7e7b7b0e9e931e24411c090e8c08dd9b42ff",
