      "writtenOn": "2020-11-15T20:08:23Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "*major #2*: this can lead to orphan config groups stored in DS which will never be referenced from ConfigHashInfo.\n\nIdea: write ConfigHashInfo first right here, referencing expected readProjectConfig.EVersion+1 (see also L154 comment). Then, when we do cleanup, all config groups are guaranteed to be referenced by a ConfigHashInfo. And, you don\u0027t need to write ConfigHashInfo when updating ProjectConfig.\n\nThe write must be transactional to ensure we don\u0027t downgrade ConfigHashInfo.ProjectEversion to lower number.\n\ntargetEversion \u003d readProjectConfig.EVersion + 1\nds.runInTransaction(\n   chi :\u003d ConfigHashInfo{...}\n  if ds.Get(chi) \u003d\u003d nil \u0026\u0026 chi.ProjectEVersion \u003e\u003d targetEversion{\n    return nil // good enough.\n  }\n  chi.ProjectEversion \u003d targetEversion \n  // set other fields.\n  return ds.Put(chi)\n}\n\nThoughts?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 147,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 148,
        "endChar": 70
      },
      "revId": "fffa7e7b7b0e9e931e24411c090e8c08dd9b42ff",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "b6d8165e_79ce09a6",
        "filename": "cv/appengine/internal/config/refresh.go",
        "patchSetId": 7
      },
      "lineNbr": 148,
      "author": {
        "id": 1381059
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-11-16T08:14:34Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027ve thought of that but I think the problem with this approach is that it may results in a ConfigHashInfo with incorrect Hash to EVersion mapping. Imaging a scenario\n  \n  T0: datastore has H0 + V0\n  T1: New Config detected, task starts updating config with H1+V1. Successfully write ConfigHashInfo but writing ProjectConfig fails.\n  T2: Config has been changed again\n  T3: A new task starts. This time the CV config in datastore is updated with H1\u0027+V1\n\nTherefore, datastore has a ConfigHashInfo with H1+V1 while in reality, V1 should maps to H1\u0027. So that\u0027s why I write ConfigHashInfo and ProjectConfig in the same transaction. I think a better way is to write ConfigHashInfo here (without a transaction) but leave the ProjectEVersion empty.\n\nIn the transaction of writing Project Config, update the ProjectEVersion of ConfigHashInfo to establish the correct mapping. \n\nThe cleanup job should delete both old versions and empty versions.",
      "parentUuid": "5ac2f928_171b27ff",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 147,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 148,
        "endChar": 70
      },
      "revId": "fffa7e7b7b0e9e931e24411c090e8c08dd9b42ff",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
