      "side": 1,
      "message": "*major #3*:\n\ngood point, but such update is likely due to competing updateProject.\n\nIf so, then we wouldn\u0027t want to update the entity blindly, as we can accidentally \"downgrade\" to an older config version. I think the right way is:\n\nbefore :\u003d ProjectConfig{...}\nds.Get(before) \nif before.ExternalHash \u003d\u003d externalHash{ return nil }\nfetch, putConfigGroups\nds.RunInTransaction(\n  pc :\u003d ProjectConfig{...}  \n  ds.Get(pc)\n  if pc.EVersion !\u003d before.EVersion {\n    return nil // Concurrent updateProject was faster. Leave it as is.\n  }\n  ...update \u0026 ds.Put(pc)\n)",
